- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the use of audit games to detect and punish insiders who inappropriately access and disclose confidential information, which is a security concern. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an FPTAS (Fully Polynomial-Time Approximation Scheme) to compute an approximately optimal solution to the non-convex optimization problem, which involves algorithmic techniques commonly used in AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the design and correctness proof of an optimization transformation, which involves algorithmic techniques commonly used in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper mentions that modern organizations such as social networks rely heavily on audit to detect and punish insiders who inappropriately access and disclose confidential information.
